data.text:
Science Space Birthday Celebration a Success

On Friday night, UOW’s Science Space celebrated its 30th birthday as an organisation. With a number of distinguished guests including Lord Mayor Gordon Bradbery, Paul Scully MP, Fiona Phillips MP and Sharon Bird MP in attendance the event celebrated Science Space’s history with flair.

Featuring special guest Graham Durant, Director of Australia’s National Science Museum Questacon, a spectacular science performance by talented Science Space ambassadors surprised and delighted the audience.

Guests were also treated to an array of innovative and high-calibre culinary treats by the newly appointed chef for UOW’s catering provider Aspire Events.

You’d be hard-pressed to find a Wollongong native who hasn’t been through the Science Space in its 30-year history. Just this year, the Science Space is on target to host 18,000 school students, out of a total of 60,000 visitors, a record number.

Be sure to check out the fantastic media coverage we received as well as our event photo album to see the full night.
